  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance alimentaire d&apos;urgence dans la provicne du Katanga</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Organization of food fairs and post-distribution monitoring</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to provide food assistance to the most vulnerable populations in Katanga province. The emergency response will be highly mobile and flexible in order to respond quickly to the most urgent needs. It will of course be coordinated with other partners in order to create synergies and complementary and integrated interventions. ACTED will organize food fairs with local traders - and from the outside if necessary - in order to reduce food insecurity for the most vulnerable populations affected by conflict. In addition, ACTED will place the protection of beneficiaries at the center of its intervention and partnership with experts from an organization specialized in this sector ( Diocesan Commission for Justice and Peace - JPEC ) will be implemented in this regard.</narrative>
  </description>
